Steps.Message: Update at 08:50 - It's Stuart from the text messaging team. We're really sorry you are waking up to no power this morning. We keep texting those signed up and will do until all customers are restored. You will need text CANCEL to 80876 to stop receiving texts (standard text fees apply). Due to the continued strong winds and heavy rain from Storm Bella across our network, we're dealing with a large amount of faults. Engineers continue to work 24/7 and are attending each job as quickly as possible. As a guide, we are hoping to have your power restored by 12:00. We'll continue to provide updates as we receive them, however you may not receive as much information as we usually like to provide. If you have any questions or concerns, please call us on 105.

We became aware of this power cut at 05:30. We’re sorry for any disruption this may have caused you. We didn’t know in advance there would be a power cut, but now that we know, our teams will do everything they can to get your power back quickly. Engineers in our control room have switched some customers power back on in your area. To get everyone’s power back on we may need to attend to investigate and make repairs. We’ll continue to update you until everyone’s power is back on.
Steps.Name: We are restoring customers automatically

Steps.Message: We have engineers on their way. As this is affecting your area, they will not need to attend your property. Rest assured once they arrive, they’ll work as quickly as is safely possible to get your power back on.
Steps.Name: Engineers on their way

Steps.Message: Engineers are now on site, carrying out investigations into the fault. Once they have completed their assessment, they will carry out repairs.
Steps.Name: Engineers investigating and fixing
